From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ask20@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Sat, 17 May 2026 08:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] netfilter: nf_flow_table_offload: log silent alloc failure

PR14o diagnostic -- the upstream flow_offload_work_add() swallows
nf_flow_offload_alloc() failures silently. When the alloc fails
(e.g. unresolved neighbour during flow_offload_eth_src/eth_dst,
or any of the five other failure sites in nf_flow_rule_route_common),
the offload work item is dropped without a single message, the
driver'\''s FLOW_CLS_REPLACE cb is never invoked, and the operator
has no way to tell from dmesg why HW offload did not engage.

On NXP LS1046A (ASK2 / ask.ko), this exact failure mode resulted in
the M2 acceptance gate (2026-05-17, ISO 2026.05.17-0738-rolling)
reporting 6.471 Gbps / 61.57 %% CPU -- the SW flowtable doing all the
forwarding work while the silicon stayed idle, and zero indication
why. The BIND eth3 / BIND eth4 traces from ask.ko fired correctly,
but REPLACE never did.

Add a net_warn_ratelimited() on the silent return path so the
failure is visible. One line, ratelimited; cannot spam the log.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <ask20@vyos-ls1046a-build>
---
 net/netfilter/nf_flow_table_offload.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/netfilter/nf_flow_table_offload.c b/net/netfilter/nf_flow_table_offload.c
index aaaaaaa..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/net/netfilter/nf_flow_table_offload.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/nf_flow_table_offload.c
@@ -974,8 +974,11 @@ static void flow_offload_work_add(struct flow_offload_work *offload)
 	int err;
 
 	err = nf_flow_offload_alloc(offload, flow_rule);
-	if (err < 0)
+	if (err < 0) {
+		net_warn_ratelimited("nf_flow_table_offload: alloc failed err=%d flow=%p cmd=%d -- HW offload silently aborted (PR14o diagnostic)\n",
+				     err, offload->flow, offload->cmd);
 		return;
+	}
 
 	err = flow_offload_rule_add(offload, flow_rule);
 	if (err < 0)
-- 
2.39.5
